comments.body:
@flomickl you are correct in your analysis.

The change I introduced does not solve this issue but rather allows the user to instruct Podman to fail when the volume does not exist instead of creating one with default setting (by adding `nocreate` to the volume options).
Once set, when the `.container` is started again (the last step in your sequence), Podman will not create the volume and instead fail to start the container.
I know it does not solve the issue, but at least it blocks unintended behaviour.

@matthijskooijman suggested we revisit the decision to set `RemainAfterExit=yes`. Would one of you care to look into it and open a PR?
